annotation.TEXT: Okay, here we go!

Alright, now that I have the silver P-switch, I want to use it in a dense enemy area, because I want to see if I can get 1-up combos from the "silver coins"! Now, bullets that are already on screen do transform into coins, but ones that are fired after the initial activation are unaffected.
Well, problem solved! I just took a hit, which removed my Flandre essence!
Hello, and welcome back to Touhou Mario! In this episode, I'm going to do a few things with the Flandre essence. First, let's go to Peaceful waterfall... (I spelled that right, didn't I?)
Killer combo! (13 hits again)

Alright, here's the Momiji battle. Now, I did try bouncing off of bullets to get up to her to see if she's stompable, and she isn't. If you try to stomp her, you'll just fall through her and take damage.
And I still managed to complete the combo, but maybe that wasn't the best example of how to use the Flandre essence for comboing, seeing how I lost it during that combo.
Oh, man. Those fireballs could've really screwed me up, but I managed to avoid them.
Killer combo! (13 hits)
Alright, it's boss time! Let's see what kind of stomping combos I can get against Wriggle!
Alright, it's boss time, against Mystia! Let's see how well I can combo against her with the Flandre essence...
Maybe if I'm at max speed... Let me clear away the nearby enemies and try that.
Triple combo! (3 hits)
Oh, over here, I can take a shortcut by doing a shell-jump... Er, I mean, an orb jump!
Bingo! I just skipped practically the whole level! Now I can fight Keine immediately!
King combo! (11 hits)

FLAWLESS VICTORY. Nice, but this is seeming less interesting than I thought it would be for some reason. Also, later bosses are going to get harder if not impossible to deal with without taking any damage (which would cost me my Flandre essence), so I'm going to stop this here.
6-life combo! Yes, I managed to grab nine "silver coins", and I did indeed get a 1-up, a 2-up, and a 3-up from it! So, I now have seven lives instead of just one!
Oh, wow, really? Did I just get through that horrid room without getting hit? Sweet! It wasn't necessary, but that was still awesome!
Killer combo! (15 hits)
And, I just took a hit and lost my B card power up, so I'm outta here.
Yeah, it's not working.
So, what's next? Well, I was wondering about one thing in the ??? level, and it involves the silver P-switch there.
FLAWLESS VICTORY. Now let's get to the real reason why I'm replaying this level...
So, now I want to go around and get the silver P-switch...

Argh. Yep. That fall down the big hole removed my power up status (probably because of how the game changed my pose during the fall). So, Satori can't be fought with the Flandre essence (or the B card, for that matter). That's a bummer.
Intentional demo count: 1

Okay, so is there a way to quickly kill myself so I can prove this? ...Yep, I just thought of a way. First I'll need a B card... (I'm surprised that I managed to hang onto the Flandre essence during all this!)

Ha, with the Flandre essence, I can get a few extra point items from these ? blocks! ...Okay, that's not really all that special, but do note how you don't visibly see a point item sprite pop out of them (like you would with coins in typical Mario games).
Not like that, unless I do a wall jump... or an orb jump! Are there any available orbs nearby?
Nuts. I didn't get very many point items there. Oh, hey... Can I shortcut to the end of the level by leaping over that pipe there?
One more lap ought to do it...
Yes, it worked! I just skipped a large portion of the level!

Awww. Well, that's a bummer. It looks like the B card doesn't work on Wriggle. I'm guessing that only Cirno is specifically coded to take damage from Mario's fireballs, so I doubt this'll work on any other boss in this hack.
I'll just quickly get another Flandre essence from Stage 1, and then I'll proceed on to Stage 2.

The Flandre essence isn't ultra vital for what I intend to try here, so it's not a big deal if I lose it. Still, it would be nice to hold onto it for a while (at least until I get to the evil homing bullets, which will almost definitely take it away).
Oh, man. Trying to stomp downward-moving bullets while I've got the ability to glide can be a pain...
Ugh, now this phase has only downward-firing bullets, and this is also the phase that eventually goes seizurific with the flashing, so I'm going to just withdraw from the battle here.

Now, upon reaching that reset door again, I've placed a savestate, because of that glitch where certain sprites in this area never respawn after being killed/used, even after resetting the room. This is just in case I screw up what I'm doing (and I did indeed screw this up a couple times, so the savestate was warranted).
DOUBLE KILL! That one was interesting.
So, this is just going to be the usual Momiji battle where I fling ten Goomba orbs at her. Maybe I should've sped up the footage even more here. Well, whatever.
Oh, was that a 1-up sound effect I just heard? But, can I get any more?
That was weird-sounding death music. Ah, but the game didn't end, because I still have 6 lives left!
Now I'll just make a couple more laps to get the rest.
I'll typically speed up the footage even more during dialog.

Okay, for the next thing on the agenda, someone wanted me to try using the B card power up on other bosses. So, let's take this B card here and double ludicrous speed (which is 16x speed) my way through Stage 1 and try it out on Wriggle...

Hmm... I wonder if this hack would've been better off with a standard lives system, along with a maximum of just 99 energy (possibly increasable to 199 from Stage 4's secret exit). Also, maybe add midpoints to most levels, and the ability to save the game normally after each level... Well anyway, what will I be doing next time? Find out next time! To be continued...
Oh, hey. I could use that power up up there since I took a hit from Wriggle.
Oh, while I'm here again, is there anything to the left? Nope.
Alright, it's boss time, against Keine! Ugh, more downward-moving bullets... Well, let's see what I can do.
Flandre essence ON! Also, I'm going to fast-forward a lot of my level-revisitng footage.
I think I'll leave most of this footage at normal speed this time.
Push! Oh, what's this? The "silver coins" are invisible! But, they are still there, and you can still collect them if you know where they are! And, if you're fast enough to collect at least seven...
Hey, that yellow fuzzball tried to get fancy there! Too bad for him that it didn't work.
Okay, let's see if I can possibly bullet hop up to that cloud...
Awesome combo! (8 hits)
Just to be sure, I'll try frying Wriggle's second phase.
Cool, I got all of the point items in that arrow.

Ah, now this is the reason I'm here. Someone suggested that I use the Flandre essence to get all of the point items here. And yes, it is now possible to do so. The upper-right-most point items in this chunk are unreachable without the ability to glide.

Now, it may look like I could just stomp the boss over and over without bouncing off of anything else, but I drop slightly lower with each stomp, and would eventually be so low that I'd take damage instead, so I still have to bounce off of other things at times.
Well, I think I got kind of lucky there. Unfortunately, this next pattern is not combo friendly. I can't bounce high enough off of Keine to be able to stomp the bullets above.
Well, let's try some other levels with the Flandre essence... I can regain the Flandre essence in Stage 1 (and some other places), thanks to the green ! blocks that are now present.
Going down! YAAAAAHHHHH!!!
Awesome! Now, let's do some left+right glitch abuse!
And now, without getting hit, make my way to the ice that's blocking the blue P-switch.

I have been so lucky with those evil homing bullets today. (Too bad I haven't been so lucky with YouTube's stupid changes to the annotation editor. I'm now in the last 5% of the video, and it's shoving the default start time back to 12:49.9 on me.) Now to fry the ice in such a way that I can get myself crushed to death!

I'm going to fast-forward through most of this, by the way. Also, UGH with the annotations now! It turns out that they start off being 5% as long as the video itself, and 5% of 16 minutes happens to be 48 seconds, which is what I was getting with my previous annotated video.

Whoops. Huh, so when the stunned orb's stun timer runs out, instead of producing a "shell-less koopa" so to speak, the orb just turns into a regular fairy maid (like how stunned koopas wake up in SMB1 and SMB3).
Honestly, I got better combos from Wriggle than from Mystia, but maybe Keine in Stage 3 will give me better results. Also, is that another potential shortcut that I'm seeing here?
Okay, now for the most combo friendly pattern that Keine has!

Their default length in this video is 40.6 seconds, which is once again, 5%. This is so stupid, because even a standard 10-minute video would have annotations starting off at 30 seconds long, which is way too long for me most of the time, and I imagine that this isn't practical for most other people either. WHAT WERE THEY THINKING?!?!
Wait, did the game take away my Flandre essence? Let me just quickly fast-forward through this conversation...
Interestingly, if you "cape spin" a winged fairy maid, you get a stunned orb that you can carry, like you'd expect. But, if you thwack it again, it goes "poof".

Okay, now I'm going to use this reset door, just to get rid of the cloud sprite, since it doesn't actually despawn when it goes off screen, and I don't want the sprite limit to interfere with what I'm planning. This'll probably cost me my Flandre essence...
Yes there is! Can I pull this off before this duder wakes up?
Blaster combo! (9 hits)
I'll leave most of this level playing at normal speed, because I do something neat at one point during it.
Well, I got the point item I missed during that jump last time.
Awww-right, it's boss time, against Wriggle once again!
The Hammer Bro. there pulled a Houdini again. Whatever.
Unfortunately, dying sets me back to just 99 energy (out of my 699 max), but that's easy to fix with the F item from the Congratulations! level.

Alright, got 'em all! Now, someone also suggested that I use the Flandre essence to help me get stomping combos on bosses. Well, since I'm close to the end of this level right now, let's start with Satori, who's the boss here.
